  "summary": "Preinstall hook exfiltrates host and user information to attacker-controlled Burp Collaborator endpoint",
  "details": "On `npm install`, package.json's `preinstall` script runs `node index.js`, which collects host identifiers (hostname, platform, arch, homedir, username/uid/gid/shell, OS info, cwd) and the output of `whoami` and `id`, then POSTs the JSON payload to a hardcoded Burp Collaborator subdomain `https://oia2jeijtfmt053ynp686t5riioac00p.oastify.com/testbydext`. The package ships no library functionality — its only effect is the install-time recon/exfiltration. Package metadata (empty description, empty author, inflated version 91.1.0, generic `@webapp-next` scope) is consistent with dependency-confusion / namespace-abuse staging.",
